{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 23:41:35.802377", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope\n- Detect anomalies, localize faulty devices, and identify root cause using live control/data-plane checks.\n\nSummary\n- Overall OSPF control-plane across core, distribution, and server access appears healthy and converged.\n- Server farm (10.200.0.0/24), DNS, and web services are reachable from most user subnets.\n- One user host exhibits broken end-to-end reachability to 10.200.0.0/24 (DNS/web), due to a local IP mask misconfiguration. This is the primary anomaly found.\n\nControl-Plane Health (OSPF)\n- Neighbors: All FRR routers report Full adjacencies (router_core_1/2/3, switch_dist_1_1, switch_dist_2_1, switch_server_access).\n  - Example: router_core_1 shows Full adjacencies on all backbone and distribution links; router_core_3 and switch_server_access adjacencies are Full; switch_server_access has 1 fully adjacent neighbor in area 0.\n- Routing tables:\n  - Core and distribution devices have correct OSPF routes to all user subnets and 10.200.0.0/24. Example: router_core_1 and router_core_2 list OSPF routes to 10.200.0.0/24 via the appropriate backbone peers; distribution switches have OSPF-learned routes to 10.200.0.0/24 via core.\n- Topology/areas:\n  - router_core_1 is ABR with area 0 and area 1 (matching hierarchical design). switch_server_access participates in area 0 for 10.200.0.0/24 and 172.16.0.22/31.\n\nData-Plane and Service Checks\n- DNS server (10.200.0.2):\n  - netstat confirms named is listening on 10.200.0.2:53 and 127.0.0.1:53.\n  - Reachable from host_1_1_1_2 and host_2_1_1_1 (ICMP pings succeed).\n- Web services:\n  - From host_2_1_1_1, curl to http://web0.local succeeds with low name lookup/connect/TTFB times (DNS resolution and HTTP path OK).\n- General reachability:\n  - Bulk reachability test shows end-to-end ICMP is broadly OK across subnets; however, entries originating from host_1_1_1_1 show failures/unknowns to remote 10.x destinations.\n\nLocalized Anomaly\n- Faulty device: host_1_1_1_1 (10.1.1.2).\n- Symptoms:\n  - Fails to ping 10.200.0.2 (dns_server) and 10.200.0.3 (web_server_0) with “Destination Host Unreachable” sourced by 10.1.1.2.\n  - Can ping local host (10.1.1.3) and can reach non-10.0.0.0/8 destinations such as 172.16.0.0 (core link).\n- Host network configuration evidence:\n  - host_1_1_1_1 IP: 10.1.1.2/8 (ifconfig netmask 255.0.0.0; ip addr shows 10.1.1.2/8).\n  - Route table includes on-link 10.0.0.0/8, and default via 10.1.1.1.\n- Contrast with a healthy peer on same LAN:\n  - host_1_1_1_2 IP: 10.1.1.3/24 (correct mask), default via 10.1.1.1. It can ping 10.200.0.2.\n\nRoot Cause\n- host_1_1_1_1 has an incorrect subnet mask (/8 instead of /24). This causes the host to:\n  - Treat all 10.0.0.0/8 addresses (including 10.200.0.0/24 and cross-site 10.2.x) as on-link.\n  - ARP for remote 10.x addresses that are not on the local L2 segment, leading to “Destination Host Unreachable” and failure to reach DNS and web servers.\n  - Non-10.x destinations (e.g., 172.16.0.0/16 infrastructure) still use the default gateway and succeed, which matches observed behavior.\n\nAdditional Notes\n- OSPF point-to-point /31 links are operating with DR/BDR elections (broadcast network type). While slightly atypical for p2p links, adjacencies are Full and stable; no evidence this impacts data-plane.\n- DNS and web services in 10.200.0.0/24 are healthy and reachable from correctly configured hosts.\n\nConclusion\n- Network-wide control and forwarding appear normal.\n- The abnormal behavior is isolated to host_1_1_1_1, with the precise root cause being a local IP mask misconfiguration (/8). This explains its inability to reach DNS and web servers in 10.200.0.0/24 and other non-local 10.x subnets, while still being able to reach 172.16.x infrastructure and same-LAN peers.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 52362, "output_tokens": 3756, "total_tokens": 56118, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 49536}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2624}}}
